<title>USA: AM Cosmetics buys Pavion for $100 mln.</title>
<headline>AM Cosmetics buys Pavion for $100 mln.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-07-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>AM Cosmetics Inc said Tuesday it completed its acquisition of Pavion Ltd of Nyack-on-Hudson, N.Y., in a transaction valued at more than $100 million in cash and stock.</p>
<p>Both companies are privately held. AM said the combined entity will have annual revenues of about $150 million, producing more than 100 million units of nail polish and 100 million units of lipstick annually.</p>
<p>Company officials were not immediately available to elaborate on the deal.</p>
